{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "lashma-webhook-integration",
    "name": "Lashma Webhook Integration",
    "description": "Webhook integration collection for Lashma Insurance App to Field Tracker",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "0"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Setup & Configuration",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "README - Start Here",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://example.com/README",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": ["example", "com"],
              "path": ["README"]
            },
            "description": "# Setup Instructions\n\n1. **Set Environment Variables:**\n   - Go to \"Environments\" tab\n   - Select or create \"Lashma Webhook\" environment\n   - Set these variables:\n     - `webhook_secret`: Your WEBHOOK_SECRET key (256-bit hex string)\n     - `base_url`: https://lashma-field-tracker-1010591944835.us-central1.run.app\n     - `agent_id`: Your internal agent UUID\n     - `agent_email`: Agent email address\n\n2. **Generate Webhook Secret (One-time):**\n   - Use the \"Generate Webhook Secret\" request to create a random secret\n   - Or provide your own 256-bit hex string\n   - Save it securely\n\n3. **Test Each Event:**\n   - Use the provided requests to send test webhooks\n   - Pre-scripts automatically generate event IDs, timestamps, and signatures\n   - Verify 200 OK responses\n\n4. **Check Logs:**\n   - Review Field Tracker logs for any errors\n   - Verify agent mapping was created\n   - Check event storage in database"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Generate Webhook Secret",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Generate a random 256-bit hex string for WEBHOOK_SECRET",
                  "const crypto = require('crypto');",
                  "const secret = crypto.randomBytes(32).toString('hex');",
                  "console.log('New Webhook Secret:', secret);",
                  "console.log('Length:', secret.length, 'characters');",
                  "console.log('Set this in your environment variables as: webhook_secret');",
                  "pm.environment.set('webhook_secret', secret);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "https://example.com",
              "protocol": "https",
              "host": ["example", "com"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Enrollment Events",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Send Enrollment Created Event",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Generate unique event ID",
                  "const timestamp = new Date().toISOString().replace(/[^0-9]/g, '').slice(0, 14);",
                  "const sequence = Math.floor(Math.random() * 10000);",
                  "const eventId = `evt_${timestamp}_enrollment_${sequence}`;",
                  "pm.environment.set('enrollment_event_id', eventId);",
                  "",
                  "// Get current ISO timestamp",
                  "const isoTimestamp = new Date().toISOString();",
                  "pm.environment.set('event_timestamp', isoTimestamp);",
                  "",
                  "// Get environment variables",
                  "const secret = pm.environment.get('webhook_secret');",
                  "const agentId = pm.environment.get('agent_id') || 'agent_uuid_test';",
                  "const agentEmail = pm.environment.get('agent_email') || 'test@lashma.com';",
                  "pm.environment.set('current_agent_id', agentId);",
                  "pm.environment.set('current_agent_email', agentEmail);",
                  "",
                  "// Build request body (compact JSON, no spaces, no signature field)",
                  "const body = JSON.stringify({",
                  "  event_type: 'enrollment_created',",
                  "  event_id: eventId,",
                  "  agent_id: agentId,",
                  "  agent_email: agentEmail,",
                  "  enrollment_count: 1,",
                  "  timestamp: isoTimestamp",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Calculate HMAC-SHA256 signature",
                  "const crypto = require('crypto');",
                  "const method = 'POST';",
                  "const uri = '/api/webhooks/insurance-events';",
                  "const payload = method + uri + body;",
                  "const signature = crypto.createHmac('sha256', secret).update(payload).digest('hex');",
                  "pm.environment.set('enrollment_signature', signature);",
                  "",
                  "// Log for debugging",
                  "console.log('Event ID:', eventId);",
                  "console.log('Timestamp:', isoTimestamp);",
                  "console.log('Agent Email:', agentEmail);",
                  "console.log('Signature:', signature.substring(0, 16) + '...');"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Verify response",
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function() {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response contains success flag', function() {",
                  "  const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(jsonData.success).to.be.true;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response contains event ID', function() {",
                  "  const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('eventId');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Log success",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  console.log('✓ Enrollment event sent successfully');",
                  "  console.log('Event ID:', pm.environment.get('enrollment_event_id'));",
                  "} else {",
                  "  console.log('✗ Error:', pm.response.text());",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{enrollment_signature}}"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"enrollment_created\",\n  \"event_id\": \"{{enrollment_event_id}}\",\n  \"agent_id\": \"{{current_agent_id}}\",\n  \"agent_email\": \"{{current_agent_email}}\",\n  \"enrollment_count\": 1,\n  \"timestamp\": \"{{event_timestamp}}\",\n  \"signature\": \"{{enrollment_signature}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/webhooks/insurance-events",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "webhooks", "insurance-events"]
            },
            "description": "Send enrollment created event to Field Tracker\n\nThis event is sent when an agent successfully enrolls a new client."
          }
        },
